latestPosts.caption:
At the inauguration of Vantara, Mrs. Nita Mukesh Ambani radiated elegance in a breathtaking handwoven Murshidabad silk saree from Swadesh. A tribute to Bengal’s rich textile heritage, the saree features traditional hand block printing, exemplifying her deep appreciation for Indian craftsmanship. A true confluence of heritage and artistry!

Curation and embroidery by: @manishmalhotra05 @manishmalhotraworld

At the Harvard India Conference, Mrs. Nita Ambani proudly announced that the Nita Mukesh Ambani Cultural Centre is set to make its mark in New York, bringing India’s rich artistic legacy to the global stage.

This September, NMACC’s maiden theatrical production Civilization to Nation and a special fashion show by Swadesh will debut at the Lincoln Center, as part of a spectacular cultural weekend showcasing the best of Indian heritage.

Stay tuned as we bring the soul of India to the heart of New York!

#NitaAmbani #HarvardIndiaConference #NMACC #NMACCinNYC #LincolnCenter #Swadesh #CivilizationToNation

Namaste NYC! A special message from Mrs. Nita M Ambani, Founder, Nita Mukesh Ambani Cultural Centre.

Join us for the #NMACCIndiaWeekend – celebrating India’s BEST in culture, music, fashion, food and art @lincolncenter

📅 Sep 12-14, 2025
📍 Lincoln Center for the Performing Arts

🚨US Premiere of India’s largest theatrical production at @LincolnCenter, NYC!

Experience ‘The Great Indian Musical: Civilization to Nation,’ a spectacular tribute to India from 5000 BC until its independence in 1947.
An NMACC presentation conceived & directed by the legendary Feroz Abbas Khan, this show is not to be missed!

Limited run, 5 PERFORMANCES ONLY!
📅 Sep 12-14, 2025
📍 David H. Koch Theater
Tickets GO LIVE on 26th June. Stay tuned!

Bring home stories etched in time from the new pavilions of Swadesh by Reliance Foundation!

Odisha’s Pattachitra and Palm Leaf Engraving are two of India’s most visually arresting narrative art forms, bringing to life epics like the Ramayana and Mahabharata through vibrant natural pigments and intricate linework.

Visit us on the Ground Floor, NMACC, and celebrate India’s living artistic traditions!

Explore the quiet luxury of India’s finest handlooms at the new pavilions of Swadesh by Reliance Foundation!

Woven in the heart of Madhya Pradesh, Chanderi & Maheshwari weaves are cherished for their silken drape, intricate patterns, and impeccable artisanship, each piece a celebration of regional heritage.

Visit us on the Ground Level, NMACC, and take home heirlooms shaped by time and tradition.

In this thoughtfully captured reflection from Design & Dialogue, hear from architects @spacedynamix, @pkdstudio_, @dwgdesigns, @jjpoonawala_design and @atelierhabib, as they reflect on their experience of engaging with heritage Indian crafts at Swadesh. 

Curated by @houseofamber_official, the evening was a quiet reaffirmation that the soul of Indian design lies not just in what we make, but in what we choose to preserve.

#DesignandDialogue #SwadeshOnline #ArtandDecor #Furniture #MadeInIndia #Architect

Centuries of craftsmanship, shaped in gold.

From Kolar, Karnataka, Kundala Velai is a jewellery style inspired by South Indian temple architecture that flourished under royal patronage. Featuring uncut diamonds, rubies, emeralds, and pearls, each piece is crafted using techniques like repoussé, chasing, and soldering with beautifully engraved backs and intricate creeper patterns.

Visit us on the Ground Level, NMACC, and take home pieces shaped by heritage and tradition.

At Design & Dialogue, Swadesh brought together @spacedynamix, @pkdstudio_, @dwgdesigns, @jjpoonawala_design and @atelierhabib—five architects with a shared reverence for the handcrafted. 

Against the backdrop of India’s richest textile and artisanal traditions,the evening hosted conversations on how heritage continues to shape space, identity and design today. Held at our Hyderabad flagship store and curated by @houseofamber_official, the gathering became a quiet ode to the design legacies that continue to shape us.

#DesignandDialogue #SwadeshOnline #ArtandDecor #Furniture #MadeinIndia #CraftsOfIndia

latestPosts.caption:
Design & Dialogue at Swadesh Hyderabad offered an evening of reflection, where conversations flowed from materials and motifs to memory and meaning. In the company of five visionary architects curated by @houseofamber_official, the event reframed Indian heritage not as a fixed past but as a living, breathing influence on modern design sensibilities. 

One that deserves not just admiration, but integration.

#DesignandDialogue #SwadeshOnline #EventsInHyderabad #ArtandDecor #InteriorDesign

At our flagship store at Alcazar Mall, Hyderabad, five distinguished architects gathered to converse beyond the confines of blueprints. Through Design & Dialogue, our flagship store hosted a resonant evening where age-old traditions and indigenous crafts became central to the conversation, not as nostalgia, but as design cues for the future.
 
Curated by @houseofamber_official, the evening explored how heritage, when understood deeply, can shape contemporary living with meaning and soul.

#HouseofAmber #DesignandDialogue #SwadeshOnline #EventsInHyderabad #ArtandDecor #HeritagePieces #Furniture
